m": "MNIST)", "context": "The Modified National Institute of Standards and Technology (MNIST) handwritten digit database, one of the most important areas of research in pattern recognition, has excellent research and practical value.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.2475992739200592}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.7141548991203308}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.038245875388383865}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.2475992739200592}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.7141548991203308}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.038245875388383865}}}, {"rawForm": "MNIST", "type": "dataset-name", "dataset-name": {"rawForm": "MNIST", "normalizedForm": "MNIST", "offsetStart": 133, "offsetEnd": 138, "boundingBoxes": [{"p": 1, "x": 282.613, "y": 662.276, "w": 33.7592, "h": 9.9289}]}, "normalizedForm": "MNIST", "context": "However, traditional image processing algorithms focusing on static feature analysis at pixel level meet tremendous difficulties in MNIST handwriting recognition due to the two primary causes: 1) the glyph information for Arabic numerals is scarce and may share common features over different numbers; 2) the handwriting varies dramatically from person to person, and some features may only occur under very specific but rare scenarios.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.2728347182273865}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.7006650567054749}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.026500128209590912}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9091970920562744}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.7006650567054749}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.19654636085033417}}}, {"rawForm": "MNIST", "type": "dataset-name", "dataset-name": {"rawForm": "MNIST", "normalizedForm": "MNIST", "offsetStart": 49, "offsetEnd": 54, "boundingBoxes": [{"p": 2, "x": 375.855, "y": 340.83, "w": 33.7603, "h": 9.9289}]}, "normalizedForm": "MNIST", "context": "As a result, using CNNs to accomplish error-free MNIST recognition remains difficult, and there really is no methodology which can reach a 100% classification performance for distinct character traits.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.30664482712745667}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.496808797121048}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.19654636085033417}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9091970920562744}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.7006650567054749}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.19654636085033417}}}, {"rawForm": "MNIST database", "type": "dataset-name", "dataset-name": {"rawForm": "MNIST database", "normalizedForm": "MNIST database", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 14, "boundingBoxes": [{"p": 5, "x": 91.8988, "y": 691.245, "w": 73.96600000000001, "h": 9.928899999999999}]}, "normalizedForm": "MNIST database", "context": "MNIST database is one of the foremost classical imaging datasets within the field of machine learning, and is broadly utilized for benchmarking in image classification.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.16748659312725067}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.744704008102417}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.08780935406684875}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8326017260551453}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.744704008102417}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.08780935406684875}}}, {"rawForm": "MNIST database", "type": "dataset-name", "dataset-name": {"rawForm": "MNIST database", "normalizedForm": "MNIST database", "offsetStart": 4, "offsetEnd": 18, "boundingBoxes": [{"p": 5, "x": 418.447, "y": 704.172, "w": 78.2758, "h": 9.928899999999999}]}, "normalizedForm": "MNIST database", "context": "The MNIST database contains 60,000 training samples and 10,000 testing samples (Table ), each consisting of a 28*28 pixel grayscale image of a handwritten Arabic digit.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8326017260551453}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.12216181308031082}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.04523641616106033}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8326017260551453}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.744704008102417}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.08780935406684875}}}, {"rawForm": "MNIST", "type": "dataset-name", "dataset-name": {"rawForm": "MNIST", "normalizedForm": "MNIST", "offsetStart": 11, "offsetEnd": 16, "boundingBoxes": [{"p": 6, "x": 71.9984, "y": 363.957, "w": 33.7603, "h": 9.9289}]}, "normalizedForm": "MNIST", "context": "Since the MNIST is a grayscale image dataset, the color channel for each image is 1 (3 for RGB images).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9091970920562744}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.053980909287929535}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.03682199865579605}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9091970920562744}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.7006650567054749}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.19654636085033417}}}, {"rawForm": "MNIST handwritten dataset", "type": "dataset-name", "dataset-name": {"rawForm": "MNIST handwritten dataset", "normalizedForm": "MNIST handwritten dataset", "offsetStart": 97, "offsetEnd": 122, "boundingBoxes": [{"p": 7, "x": 366.62, "y": 142.571, "w": 120.69241249999999, "h": 9.928899999999999}]}, "normalizedForm": "MNIST handwritten dataset", "context": "This shows that the learning rate decay can effectively improve the recognition accuracy of the MNIST handwritten dataset.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.4753445088863373}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.414923757314682}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.10973172634840012}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.4753445088863373}, "created": {"value": false, "sco